Package edu.stanford.cfuller.imageanalysistools.image

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Image
    Represents a multidimensional image with some pixel data and associated metadata.
    WritableImage
    Represents a read/write multidimensional image with some pixel data and associated metadata.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BasicPixelData
    Holds image pixel data in a type-independent manner; handles conversion to the appropriate number format for the data being stored to disk.
    DimensionFlipper
    A Class that swaps two dimensions of an Image.
    Histogram
    This class represents a histogram of intensity values in an Image.
    ImageCoordinate
    Represents an integer-valued coordinate in an n-dimensional image.
    ImageFactory
    A Factory for creating new objects implementing the Image and WritableImage interfaces.
    ImageIterator
    This class implements the Iterator required for foreach-style looping through the coordinates in an Image
    ImageIterator5D
    An iterator optimized for faster iteration over 5D images.
    ImagePlusPixelData
    A type of WritablePixelData that uses an ImageJ ImagePlus as its underlying representation.
    ImageSet
    A set of related Images that will be processed together for analysis.
    ImageSet.ImageHolder  
    ImgLibPixelData
    A type of WritablePixelData that uses an ImgLib2 ImgPlus as its underlying representation.
    PixelData
    PixelData objects hold the (5-dimensional X, Y, Z, channel, time) image values themselves for classes implementing Image.
    PixelDataFactory
    A factory to construct PixelData objects; the choice of implementation will be made based on the properties of the data.
    ReadOnlyImageImpl
    A basic read-only implementation of Image.
    WritableImageImpl
    A basic read-write implementation of WritableImage.
    WritablePixelData
    An extension of a PixelData object that also supports writing of image data.
